(499, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2012/08/state-of-the-word-2012/'' title=''I had an amazing weekend at WordCamp San Francisco hanging out with hundreds of WordPress users from all over the world at the main event and the dev day afterward. Then on Sunday I was humbled to be featured on the cover of my hometown paper the Houston Chronicle in an article David Kaplan wrote following the 10-year high school reunion I went to (PDF). If  [&hellip;]''>Matt: State of the Word 2012</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.tv/2012/08/06/matt-mullenweg-state-of-the-word-2012/'' title='' [&hellip;]''>WordPress.tv: Matt Mullenweg: State of the Word 2012</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://buddypress.org/2012/08/buddypress-1-6-is-now-available/'' title=''BuddyPress 1.6 “Lucali” is here! Version 1.6 is a major feature release for BuddyPress, introducing several hundred of bug fixes, dozens of enhancements, and several major, all-new features. Whether you’ve never used BuddyPress before or are a longtime BP guru, you’re in for a treat. BuddyPress 1.6 is the most feature-rich, secure, stable, and fun-to-use ver [&hellip;]''>BuddyPress: BuddyPress 1.6 is now available!</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/CALf-isQJ6o/'' title=''New plugins WP Database Cleaner allows you to cleanup and optimize the WordPress database by removing all spam comments, trash comments, unused tags, post revisions, auto drafts, and much more. WP Search for Comments enables you to search in comments separetly from the search loop. Updated plugins Jetpack allows you to supercharge your WordPress site with po [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 8/5</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ocaoimh.ie/2012/08/03/search-twitter-with-tweet-tweet/'' title=''My Tweet Tweet plugin hasn’t been updated in a while. It stores Twitter conversations in your local database. Not just your own tweets but also the tweets of those you follow. Storage can be a problem once the plugin has been running for a few months however. The log table gets quite big so last year I added code to the plugin that broke up those tables once [&hellip;]''>Donncha: Search more Twitter with Tweet Tweet</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
